Initial prototype for Karlstadt 2026 Election Dashboard

This commit introduces a functional prototype for the Karlstadt 2026
local election dashboard, currently utilizing historical 2020 election
data from AKDB/Votemanager for testing and layout purposes.

Core functionalities implemented:
- Python Backend (`fetcher.py`): Scrapes official AKDB HTML results,
  parsing both aggregate party strength charts and complex candidate
  tables to construct a clean `live_data.json`.
- Frontend UI (`index.html`): Responsive, mobile-first design using
  Tailwind CSS and Alpine.js. Features fuzzy search, party toggles,
  and Chart.js integration for visual data representation.
- Environment & Formatting: Added `requirements.txt`, rigidly linted
  code using `black` and `flake8`, and defined agent instructions in
  `CONTRIBUTING.md`.
- Documentation: Created `README.md` with detailed local Wi-Fi hosting
  instructions, and `Observations.md` outlining the critical correlation
  between HTML results and downloadable CSVs for future fallback plans.
- Licensing: Attached official MIT License template from choosealicense.
